        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>USA, Assistant Chief of Staff for Operations, U.S. Army, until February 12, 1951; promoted to Lieutenant General and appointed Deputy Chief of Staff for Plans, U.S. Army, February 13, 1951.</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1951v05/persons#p_BCL1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="1">
            <p>Lieutenant General, United States Army, Chairman of the Inter-American Defense Board from January 2, 1951 until August 4, 1952.</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1952-54v04/persons#p_BCL1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="2">
            <p>USA, Assistant Chief of Staff for Operations until August 1952; Commander of the Seventh Army in Germany, August 1952–April 1953; Commander in Chief, U.S. Army in Europe, April–October 1953; thereafter, Vice Chief of Staff of the Army.</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1952-54v09p1/persons#p_BGCL1</source-url>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1952-54v09p2/persons#p_BGCL1</source-url>
        </remark>
        <remark source-urls="2">
            <p>USA, Assistant Chief of Staff for Operations until August 1952; Commander of the 7th Army in Germany, August 1952–April 1953; Commander in Chief, U.S. Army in Europe, April-October 1953; thereafter, Vice Chief of Staff of the Army.</p>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1952-54v11p1/persons#p_BGCL1</source-url>
            <source-url>https://history.state.gov/historicaldocuments/frus1952-54v11p2/persons#p_BGCL1</source-url>
